      'The table shows the number of bases in a single DNA strand that codes for a strand of mRNA. The strand contains no introns.\nThe letters X, Y and Z represent the percentage of each type of base in the mRNA.\nBasesNumber of kilobases (kb) in the DNA strandPercentage of same bases in the mRNAAdenine3123.3Cytosine22XGuanine26YThymine24Z\nWhich option shows the correct percentages of bases in the mRNA synthesised?\n\n\n\n- A.$\\hspace{1em}$ X = 25.2%, Y= 21.4%, Z = 30.1%\n- B.$\\hspace{1em}$ X = 21.4%, Y = 25.2%, Z = 23.3%\n- C.$\\hspace{1em}$ X = 25.2%, Y = 21.4%, Z = 0%\n- D.$\\hspace{1em}$ X = 21.4%, Y = 25.2%, Z = 0%\n',
